                 Step 1: Install Node.js & npm

Tailwind requires Node.js to work.

1.Go to Node.js official website
2.Download the LTS version (recommended for stability).
3.Install it.
4.Verify installation by opening VS Code terminal (Ctrl + ~) and typing:
node -v
npm -v
        Step 2: Create a Project Folder

Open VS Code.
Create a folder for your project (e.g., mule).
Open this folder in VS Code (File â†’ Open Folder).
     Step 3: Initialize npm

In the VS Code terminal, run:
npm init -y
This creates a package.json file (needed to manage Tailwind and other packages).
Step 4: Install Tailwind CSS

Run:npm install -D tailwindcss@3.4.17 postcss autoprefixer
create two files:

tailwind.config.js â†’ Tailwind configuration
postcss.config.js â†’ PostCSS setup
Step 5: Configure Tailwind
Open tailwind.config.js and set the content paths so Tailwind knows where to look for class names:
/** @type {import('tailwindcss').Config} */
module.exports = {
  content: ["./*.html"], // or "./src/**/*.{html,js}" if you have src folder
  theme: {
    extend: {},
  },
  plugins: [],
}
Step 6: Create CSS File
Create a CSS file (e.g., style.css).
Add Tailwind directives:
@tailwind base;
@tailwind components;
@tailwind utilities;
      Step 7: Build Tailwind CSS
In the terminal, run:
npx tailwindcss -i ./style.css -o ./output.css --watch
-i â†’ input file (style.css)
-o â†’ output file (output.css)
--watch â†’ automatically rebuild on changes
Now, whenever you save your CSS or HTML, Tailwind will update automatically. âœ…
         Step 8: Link Output CSS in HTML

In your HTML file:<link href="output.css" rel="stylesheet">
Optional VS Code Tips

Install Tailwind CSS IntelliSense extension â†’ gives autocomplete for Tailwind classes.

Use Live Server extension â†’ refresh browser automatically when you save HTML.

ðŸ’¡ Tip: The --watch flag in Step 7 is key â€” it replaces the need to manually run npm run build every time you change a class.
          Step 9: create index.html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
    <link href="output.css" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body>
<body class="min-h-screen flex items-center justify-center bg-slate-600">
 <div class="bg-orange-600 p-8 rounded-xl shadow-lg w-96">
 <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-center mb-6">Login</h2>
<input type="email" placeholder="Email"
 class="w-full mb-4 px-4 py-3 border rounded-lg">
 <input type="password" placeholder="Password"
 class="w-full mb-4 px-4 py-3 border rounded-lg">
 <button
 class="w-full bg-blue-600 text-white py-3 rounded-lg">
 Login
 </button>
 </div>
</body>
</html>

